            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "@ZyX-I \nThanks for looking into this!\n\nBut I don't know what's advertized in this regard (I don't watch much TV ;).\n\nAfter `set shada+='X` it gets appended and is unclear how that is handled, e.g. with `shada=!,'1000,<50,s10,h,%,'2000`.\nIs the latest value being used?\n\nApart from that I can see that `'shada'` is similar to Vim's `'viminfo'`, but it's a new setting after all and could work better.\n\nI can  see that the current workaround would be to use `substitute` on `&shada`, but after all it should be improved in Neovim itself, at least with regard to the documentation.\n",
