            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "@blueyed It works exactly like advertised in `:h set+=`, except that preventing duplicates is advertised for flag options (which is why I consider this a bug). And any new setting is using the same facility, so there is no reason it can work better. Used value is the first one. Any values after `n` are ignored (any values after `n` are considered to be part of `n` argument).\n",
